metadata.name: Departure Within Shattered Windmills #226
metadata.description:
I wrote the following when reviewing the outputs...

The wind is gone,
My windmill falls,
I reach out to catch the pieces.
Half fall in my right hand,
The others in my left,
Two stacks of colored paper.
I’m holding my windmill,
I feel the breeze in my hair.
Each hand is empty,
My windmill rises,
I can see the wind.

'Departure Within Shattered Windmills' was originally inspired by suprematism, and then started to gain more complexity. It is still a combination of simple features, subdivided quads drawn on different planes of perspective. Chaos simulated by many organized grids. Countless pieces of a windmill.

25% of the royalties for each edition will pass to the original minter.

Each output is generated from code written in p5js.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: ROIL #70
metadata.description:
This space filling algorithm explores a range of abstract outputs. A chaotic composition is formed as it mutates and interferes with itself along the way. It finishes when the canvas has been fully covered. There are 20 color palettes inspired by natural phenomena. It was programmed from scratch in vanilla JavaScript.

Controls
1 - Save a png
2 - Randomize
3 - Enable HD (6300x8192)

Code and Outputs are Copyright (C) 2022 Frank Force
Artwork is released under CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Wild Matrix #382
metadata.description:
Wild Matrix art project are just patterns, all kind, created using triangles, rectangles, squares and a lot of colors :)

If you like patterns -> be wild, mint free a Wild Matrix!

25% of secondary sales goes to Proceesing Foundation (let's encourage and sustain generative art) | 25% of secondary sales goes to SavePakistan (let's help people in need). 

I would kindly appreciate a share, a follow of my Twitter or just make your mint know to others if you like it. 

–--
Maid with joy and excitment in p5js.
k@in, November 2022

metadata.name: Meaning #179
metadata.description:
It is what we seek our entire lives, but only very few of us are able to find it. If only we did not keep looking for it elsewhere, while it always was where it always has been...

* * *

Press S to save as PNG.

To save a larger image, open live view, add "&s=WIDTH_IN_PIXELS" to the end of the URL, press Enter and then press S.

Artwork by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
